<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOTNOTES-REVIEW-2TAKES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HYPERLINKS REPLACE THOSE OLD-FASHIONED FOOTNOTES 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(Eds: The numbers in parentheses correspond to the footnotes at the
end of the article. The word TILDE in parentheses has been used
instead of the symbol, which is nontransmittable to many newspaper
systems.) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For use by special arrangement
only. Asian and European points: Call Karl Horwitz in Paris for
details and prices. Phone: 47 42 17 11; fax: 47-42-80-44. 
