<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, July 16 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   MASRY-TVSHOW (BURBANK, Calif.) _ Portrayed by actor Albert
Finney in this year's Julia Roberts blockbuster, ``Erin
Brockovich,'' Edward Masry is now starring in his own courtroom
drama. ``Power of Attorney'' -- a cross between ``Judge Judy'' and
``L.A. Law'' -- debuts Aug. 28, featuring Gloria Allred,
Christopher Darden and other high-profile attorneys. By Cecilia
Chan. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   EYESIGHT-IMPLANTS (LOS ANGELES) _ Encroaching on the domain of
miracles, a biotechnology firm hopes to restore long-term vision to
blind people as early as next year, using retinal implants. Second
Sight President Dr. Robert Greenberg said use of his implant is a
``when'' rather than ``if'' proposition, now that a key threshold
-- wireless transmission of images to the retina -- appears to have
been crossed. By Robert Monroe. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CANCERKIDS-GAMES (PALMDALE, Calif.) _ When she was diagnosed
with leukemia two years ago, 11-year-old Brittany McDaniels vowed
to battle the disease and has since expended her formidable
energies on raising thousands of dollars to find a cure and helping
others like her. Her latest crusade is to raise money to buy
Nintendo 64 video games to replace the ones stolen from the
pediatric oncology clinic where she receives chemotherapy
treatments. By Karen Maeshiro. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
