<HEADLINE>
REFINING THE CAT'S-EYE VIEW OF THE COSMOS 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(Eds: Boldface `it' in 9th graf should be set in italics.) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For use by special arrangement
only. Asian and European points: Call Karl Horwitz in Paris for
details and prices, phone: 47 42 17 11; fax: 47-42-80-44.) 
 By GEORGE JOHNSON   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Startling as life in the subatomic realm can seem, with
particles existing both here and there or darting to and fro at the
same time, people have been able to take some small comfort in
knowing that the ``real'' world doesn't work that way. Though made
