prestigious post that she will likely hold until mandatory
retirement in 20 years. She will spend her first four years
supervising AME churches in southern Africa. Triumphant after the
election at the church's quadrennial convention in Cincinnati, she
said from the podium, ``The stained glass ceiling has been
pierced.''
</P>
<P>
   _ LAURIE GOODSTEIN
</P>
<P>
   Look. Up in the Sky ...
</P>
<P>
   The stalled effort to build the International Space Station
