module. The 20-ton craft, which is to serve as the orbital
outpost's crucial command and living section during early stages of
construction, began a series of maneuvers and tests aimed at having
it dock with the nascent station on July 25.
</P>
<P>
   With Zvezda in place, the United States and 15 partner nations
can end an 18-month building hiatus primarily caused by Russia's
