had traveled a very long road to get Zvezda launched, Yuri Koptev,
head of the Russian Space Agency, thanked project partners for
their patience and support. ``We wish this road had been a highway,
but a highway it was not,'' he said. ``It was oftentimes closed for
repairs. We have experienced detours, bumps and holes.''
</P>
<P>
   _ WARREN E. LEARY
</P>
<P>
   Israel Stops a Sale to China
</P>
<P>
   In a precisely timed decision, the Israeli government announced
the cancellation of a $250 million sale of a sophisticated airborne
