members of Congress. Prime Minister Ehud Barak told President
Clinton of his decision on the first night of the Camp David
summit. The next morning, congressional critics praised Barak. The
issue had become so heated that military aid to Israel was
threatened in the Congress.
</P>
<P>
   _ JANE PERLEZ
</P>
<P>
   A Grim AIDS Conference
</P>
<P>
   Dashing the hopes of thousands of scientists gathered in Durban,
