<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-AFC-CAPSULES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AFC TRAINING CAMP CAPSULES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE BAMBACH 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
BALTIMORE RAVENS
<TEXT>
<P>
   PLAYERS REPORT: July 23, Western Maryland College, Westminster,
Md.
</P>
<P>
   1999: 8-8, 3rd in AFC Central
</P>
<P>
   KEY ADDITIONS: TE Shannon Sharpe, DT Sam Adams
</P>
<P>
   KEY LOSSES: RB Errict Rhett, OG Jeff Blackshear
</P>
<P>
   THINGS TO DO: Ensure QB Tony Banks is comfortable in new-look
offense featuring rookies RB Jamal Lewis and WR Travis Taylor, and
free-agent TE Shannon Sharpe. LB Ray Lewis must put tumultuous
off-season behind him.
</P>
<P>
   PRESEASON SCHEDULE Aug. 5 Philadelphia 7 p.m. Aug. 12 N.Y. Jets
7 p.m. Aug. 18 at Carolina 7 p.m. Aug. 25 at N.Y. Giants 7 p.m.
BUFFALO BILLS
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS REPORT: Thursday, St. John Fisher College, Pittsford,
N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   1999: 11-5, 2nd in AFC East
</P>
<P>
   KEY LOSSES: DE Bruce Smith, RB Thurman Thomas, WR Andre Reed, FB
Sam Gash, S Kurt Schulz
</P>
<P>
   KEY ADDITIONS: None
</P>
<P>
   THINGS TO DO: Settle quarterback controversy between Rob
Johnson, whom Wade Phillips said will start, and Doug Flutie. Find
starter at free safety; establish Antowain Smith as starting RB.
</P>
<P>
   PRESEASON SCHEDULE Aug. 4 Cincinnati 6:30 p.m. Aug. 12 at
Detroit 7:20 p.m. Aug. 19 at St. Louis 7 p.m. Aug. 24 at
Philadelphia 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   CINCINNATI BENGALS
</P>
<P>
