<BODY>
 BC_ARZ-BUDGET  
HMO - A health care meltdown in rural Arizona this summer is
forcing elderly residents to go to Mexico for affordable drugs, lie
about their addresses to maintain coverage and take menial jobs to
help pay for their care. Many retirees in rural communities are
cutting back on their medications because the HMO programs that
recently provided prescription benefits are gone. Story will move
in the ``A'' category.
<TEXT>
<P>
   HMOSIDE -About 13,000 seniors are getting the boot Jan. 1 from
Medicare HMOs, the latest in a wave of exits that has pushed out
54,200 rural Arizonans from the federal health insurance program
since 1998.
</P>
<P>
   That leaves only one rural Arizona county, Santa Cruz, with an
HMO, a stark change from a few years ago, when rural Arizona was a
national model for its numerous choices in health care delivery.
Story will move in the `A' category.
</P>
<P>
   WNBA - By the measures of TV deals and sponsorship packages, as
well as player salaries and fan support, the WNBA doesn't come
close to the elite ranks of men's professional sports. Even still,
as the league readies for its biggest event of the year, the 2000
WNBA All-Star Game, to be played at America West Arena on Monday
night, there are subtle signs the WNBA is making its mark in the
cluttered iconography of American sports. Story will move in the
``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) {ndash} City Planning Department
Director Dave Richert did not curse at the two Latino men at the
meeting. He didn't use an ethnic slur. He didn't threaten anyone.
It doesn't matter. He was accused of being racist and, these days,
being called a racist is as bad as being one. Worse, if it gets in
the paper. By E.J. MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories.
</P>
<P>
   ZUNI-BOOKS- Cultural anthropologist Nancy Yaw Davis has a
revolutionary theory: The Zuni people of North America are
descendents of 14th century Japanese Buddhist monks. So far, her
colleagues are dismissing her ideas, but, she says, ``I've got them
nervous.'' By BARBARA YOST. Story will move in the ``E'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
